            <thetext>Created attachment 1165
Subclass as workaround

qx.ui.table.cellrenderer.AbstractImage and qx.ui.table.cellrenderer.Image provide a tooltip that comes from the &quot;cellinfo&quot;. But there is no possibility to set the tooltip to the &quot;cellinfo&quot;.

The attached class is a subclass of qx.ui.table.cellrenderer.Image that basically only creates the &quot;cellinfo&quot; anew. Therefore the cellinfo.value contains a struct with the image url and tooltip instead of the plain url string. With this subclass as workaround everything works as expected. But it&#39;s only a workaround.</thetext>
          </long_desc>
